taxon.name: Geranium robertianum

default_photo.attribution: W.carter, no known copyright restrictions (public domain)

taxon.wikipedia_summary: Geranium robertianum, commonly known as herb-Robert, red robin, death come quickly, storksbill, fox geranium, stinking Bob, squinter-pip (Shropshire), crow's foot, or (in North America) Roberts geranium, is a common species of cranesbill native to Europe and parts of Asia, North America, and North Africa.
